item.title: CVE-2016-8923|2024-08-06T02:35:02.253Z -- ibm -- curam%20social%20program%20management
item.description: IBM Curam Social Program Management 5.2, 6.0, and 7.0 contains a vulnerability that would allow an authorized user to obtain sensitive information from the profile of a higher privileged user that they should not have access to. IBM X-Force ID: 118536.

item.title: CVE-2016-9978|2024-08-06T03:07:31.385Z -- ibm -- curam%20social%20program%20management
item.description: IBM Curam Social Program Management 5.2, 6.0, and 7.0 could allow an authenticated attacker to disclose sensitive information. IBM X-Force ID: 120254.

item.title: CVE-2016-9979|2024-08-06T03:07:31.640Z -- ibm -- curam%20social%20program%20management
item.description: IBM Curam Social Program Management 5.2, 6.0, and 7.0 is vulnerable to cross-site scripting. This vulnerability allows users to embed arbitrary JavaScript code in the Web UI thus altering the intended functionality potentially leading to credentials disclosure within a trusted session. IBM X-Force ID: 120255.
